      504.25,
      497.68,
      517.87
    ],
    "text": "SC/Appeal/71/2024 filed by the Petitioners-Appellants (\u201cAppellants\u201d) of this case.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      534.97,
      543.07,
      548.59
    ],
    "text": "The 1st Respondent-Respondent (\u20181st Respondent\u2019) made an application to the 2nd",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      555.73,
      542.97,
      569.35
    ],
    "text": "Respondent-Respondent, the People\u2019s Bank, under the provisions of the Finance Act, No. 11",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      576.49,
      543.15,
      590.11
    ],
    "text": "of 1963, for the redemption of the land described therein as Mahalindawatte. The 3rd",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT",
      "Calisto MT,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      597.49,
      542.9,
      611.11
    ],
    "text": "Respondent-Respondent (\u201c3rd Respondent\u201d) was appointed by the said 2nd Respondent to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      618.28,
      542.92,
      631.9
    ],
    "text": "conduct an inquiry into the said application. The Appellants sought a writ of certiorari in the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      639.16,
      543.14,
      652.78
    ],
    "text": "Court of Appeal to quash the order marked \u2018Y4\u2019 delivered by the 3rd Respondent, contending",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      660.04,
      407.29,
      673.66
    ],
    "text": "that the said order is null and void and of no force or avail in law.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      726.83,
      542.54,
      756.12
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Aptos",
      "Aptos,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.96,
      542.87,
      85.58
    ],
    "text": "The 2nd and 3rd Respondents raised several preliminary objections in the Court of Appeal",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.72,
      543.04,
      106.34
    ],
    "text": "and moved for the dismissal of the said application in limine. The Court of Appeal considered,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      113.6,
      251.03,
      127.22
    ],
    "text": "inter alia, the following objections:",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      144.32,
      542.88,
      157.94
    ],
    "text": "1. that the application is futile, inasmuch as the relief sought does not finally adjudicate",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      165.08,
      542.86,
      178.7
    ],
    "text": "the rights of the Petitioners nor dispose of the matter relating to the redemption of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      185.96,
      195.47,
      199.58
    ],
    "text": "subject property;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      216.68,
      542.8,
      230.3
    ],
    "text": "2. that the writ of certiorari is sought not against a determination but merely against a",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      237.56,
      418.33,
      251.18
    ],
    "text": "recommendation, which is not amenable to Judicial Review;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.02,
      268.19,
      542.85,
      281.81
    ],
    "text": "3. that the Petitioners have failed to implead the necessary parties required for the",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      108.02,
      289.07,
      279.83,
      302.69
    ],
    "text": "adjudication of the reliefs sought.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      319.79,
      543.07,
      333.41
    ],
    "text": "By its Order dated 22 June 2020, the Court of Appeal upheld the preliminary objection based",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      340.55,
      542.88,
      354.17
    ],
    "text": "on futility, holding that the application was unsustainable in law since the Appellants had",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      361.31,
      543.11,
      374.93
    ],
    "text": "failed to challenge the determination made by the Board of Directors of the People\u2019s Bank,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      382.07,
      542.8,
      395.69
    ],
    "text": "which would remain operative even if the impugned order of the 3rd Respondent were to be",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      402.83,
      542.89,
      416.45
    ],
    "text": "quashed. However, the Court of Appeal rejected the contention that the recommendation of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      423.71,
      543.13,
      437.33
    ],
    "text": "the 3rd Respondent was not amenable to Judicial Review. Further, no specific order has been",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      444.61,
      352.93,
      458.23
    ],
    "text": "made on the objection relating to the necessary parties.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      475.21,
      542.81,
      488.83
    ],
    "text": "Being aggrieved by the said Order, the Appellants sought and obtained Special Leave to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      496.09,
      357.01,
      509.71
    ],
    "text": "Appeal to this Court on the following Question of Law:",
    "fonts": [
      "Calisto MT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
